@startuml d1-information-model
!theme plain
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam packageStyle frame
skinparam linetype ortho

title Herold — D1 Information Model

' Non-trivial domain data types referenced below (Identifier,
' OpaqueSecret, NoteStatusDT, IssueStateDT, MessageTypeDT,
' TypeSpecificData) are defined in D2. Trivial types (Text, Integer,
' Boolean, Date, Email, URL, Timestamp, Markdown) are used at face
' value.

' ============================================================
' Herold data — local persistence (application database + local file store)
' ============================================================
package "Herold data" <<Frame>> #E8F4FF {

  class Operator {
    + id : Identifier
    + name : Text
    + email : Email
    + apiKeyHash : OpaqueSecret [0..1]
    + totpSecret : OpaqueSecret [0..1]
    + totpConfirmedAt : Timestamp [0..1]
  }
  note left of Operator
    Single-operator system. At most one Operator
    instance exists at any time
    (CON-3a-04 *Single-User System*).
    **apiKeyHash** is the first-factor verifier:
    the operator presents the raw API key at sign-in,
    the system compares its hash in constant time.
    **totpSecret** + **totpConfirmedAt** form the
    second factor (RFC 6238 TOTP, UC-02).
  end note

  class RecoveryToken <<file>> {
    + token : OpaqueSecret
    + placedAt : Timestamp
  }
  note left of RecoveryToken
    Single transient artefact placed by the operator
    out-of-band on the host (e.g. via FTP) when
    locked out. At most one exists at any time.
    TTL is enforced relative to **placedAt**
    (NFR-15a-04, 60 minutes).
    Redemption (UC-03) deletes the artefact, unbinds
    the bound TOTP, rotates **Operator.apiKeyHash**,
    and surfaces the new API key to the operator
    exactly once.
  end note

  class VoiceNote {
    + id : Identifier
    + type : MessageTypeDT
    + status : NoteStatusDT
    + audioPath : Text [0..1]
    + transcript : Text [0..1]
    + processedTitle : Text [0..1]
    + processedBody : Markdown [0..1]
    + metadata : TypeSpecificData [0..1]
    + githubIssueNumber : Integer [0..1]
    + githubIssueUrl : URL [0..1]
    + errorMessage : Text [0..1]
    + createdAt : Timestamp
    + updatedAt : Timestamp
  }
  note right of VoiceNote
    **type** classifies the note (MessageTypeDT enum).
    The slot inventory of **metadata** is fixed per
    type at spec level (see D2.7). The host configures,
    per type, the prompt and the GitHub label written
    on dispatch.
    When the note reaches **sent**, **githubIssueNumber**
    and **githubIssueUrl** point to the created issue.
  end note

  enum NoteStatusDT <<D2>> {
    recorded
    processed
    sent
  }

  enum MessageTypeDT <<D2>> {
    general
    youtube
    diary
    obsidian
    todo
  }

  ' Layout hints: Operator top-left, RecoveryToken below Operator,
  ' VoiceNote to the right of Operator.
  Operator       -[hidden]down-  RecoveryToken
  Operator       -[hidden]right- VoiceNote
  VoiceNote      -[hidden]down-  NoteStatusDT
  NoteStatusDT     -[hidden]right- MessageTypeDT
}

' ============================================================
' Ticket data — lives outside Herold's process boundary
' ============================================================
package "Ticket data" <<Frame>> #FFF4E0 {

  class GitHubIssue {
    + number : Integer
    + url : URL
    + title : Text
    + body : Markdown
    + labels : Set<Text>
    + state : IssueStateDT
  }
  note right of GitHubIssue
    GitHubIssue lives at GitHub. Herold persists only
    **VoiceNote.githubIssueNumber** (→ **number**) and
    **VoiceNote.githubIssueUrl** (→ **url**). The other
    attributes describe the **structure Herold writes
    on dispatch** (UC-08).
  end note

  class GitHubRepository {
    + owner : Text
    + name : Text
  }
  note right of GitHubRepository
    Fixed at the host level by configuration.
  end note

  enum IssueStateDT <<D2>> {
    open
    closed
  }

  GitHubIssue -[hidden]down- IssueStateDT
}

' ============================================================
' Relationships
' ============================================================

VoiceNote ..>            NoteStatusDT     : status
VoiceNote ..>            MessageTypeDT  : type
VoiceNote ..>            GitHubIssue    : refers to
GitHubIssue ..>          IssueStateDT   : state

GitHubRepository "1" --> "*" GitHubIssue : contains

' Stack the two packages vertically: Herold data on top,
' Ticket data at the bottom.
NoteStatusDT    -[hidden]down- GitHubIssue
MessageTypeDT -[hidden]down- GitHubRepository

@enduml
